With insolent triumph Phormio discloses to the outraged wife her husband’s insamy. Demipho tries to intercede for his wretched brother, at first with small success. Phormio improves the occasion. He wins from Nausistrata a practical assurance that Phaedria shall be allowed to keep his bride, that the money paid shall not be asked for, and last, but not least, an invitation for himself to supper, to which they all go in as the curtain falls ¹.
